    AddressParseException, DocumentNavigatorException, DuplicateReceiptException, EmptyReceiptListException, UnsupportedCurrencyException, UnsupportedFormatException, ValidationException

    public class ParserException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
    Base exception class for any errors that occur within the parsers.

    In general, parsers should throw this exception if an unhandled or unexpected error occurs during the parsing of the content. If there is a use-case that is purposefully not being handled for, parsers should override this exception and throw a more concrete exception type. An example of this would be the AddressParseException class.

    The exception type is automatically parsed and stored with the failed content and provides a basis for error filtering/reporting for the receipt framework.
